‘ The gods accept the humble offerings of humble people. Mod- eration‚ simplicity‚ thrift, content with our own station, have place in religious observance as well as in other phases of life.’ This is all the doctrine of the Ode. The name Phidyle (Gr. fem. of Φειδύλος, see Lidd. and Scott, s.v. φειδός), is clearly chosen to characterize a ‘ thrifty’ Sabine housewife.
